{
  "texts": [
    "Two models were separately trained for the classification of XRD patterns and virtual PDFs in each chemistry that we tested (Supplementary Table 1).",
    "Both models share the same input size (4501 values), being equal to the number of datapoints in each XRD pattern or virtual PDF.",
    "They also share the same output size, which is set by the number of reference phases included in the training set.",
    "Each neuron in the output layer represents a distinct phase that may be output by the CNN at inference.",
    "The two models have similar architectures that differ only in their convolution layers."
  ]
}